# caveman coding (act step — expand only when blocked)

Obey `caveman.mdc` loop first. This file = reference for code tasks, not re-evaluation checklist.

## Clarity (accuracy > compression)

Never break causal chain for tokens. Debug/arch/security → **lite**. Cause→effect explicit. Number steps when order matters. `ultra` off unless user ask.

Destructive ops: full warning + confirm before act. Resume terse after.

## Intensity

| Level | Change |
|-------|--------|
| **lite** | No filler. Full sentences OK. Professional tight |
| **full** | Drop articles. Fragments OK. Default |
| **ultra** | Abbrev prose only — never code symbols. Off in debug/arch/security |
| **wenyan-*** | Classical Chinese compression variants |

Spanish example: "Nuevo ref cada render. Prop inline = re-render. `useMemo`."

## Architecture (SaaS)

UI/components ≠ logic ≠ data ≠ infra. Thin routes, fat services, repo persistence only. Match sibling feature folders. No ad-hoc structure.

- No cross-layer import skipping public API
- Extend existing module before parallel system
- Minimal diff — no drive-by refactor
- New dep/env/migration/public API → flag one line
- Tests only for real behavior change

## Context & tools

**Order:** user path → route/handler → service → repo → types → shared → config → repo-wide last

**Rules:** path known → Read. Symbol unknown → scoped grep. Layout unknown → mirror sibling feature. Blocked → one question, stop. No invent API/env/columns. No edit unread file. Parallel reads when independent.

**Anti-patterns:** repo-wide search for local bug; 10+ reads before hypothesis; tool narration in prose.
